## The Core Idea

Enterprises separate:

### 🏗 Platform Layer

Shared infrastructure & controls:

* Hub VNet
* Firewall
* Log Analytics
* Policies
* Monitoring
* Key Vault (shared)
* Identity controls

Managed by:
Platform / Cloud / Infra team

---

### 🚀 Workload Layer

Applications & business systems:

* Dev environment
* Prod environment
* App VMs
* App Services
* Databases

Managed by:
App teams

---

## Why This Separation Is Critical

### 1️⃣ Security Isolation

If an app team misconfigures something:

* They don’t control firewall
* They don’t control policies
* They can’t break governance

---

### 2️⃣ Clear Responsibility

Platform Team:

* Networking
* Identity
* Policies
* Logging

App Team:

* Deploy app
* Scale app
* Maintain app

No confusion.

---

### 3️⃣ Scale

When company grows:

* You add new workload subscriptions
* Platform stays stable

---

### Interview Gold Line

> We separate platform from workloads to enforce centralized governance and minimize blast radius while allowing application teams to operate independently.

